UGHELLI – People’s Democratic Party PDP Councilors’ Forum has said that Former Vice President, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar mission for Nigeria in 2023 and beyond is a rescue mission just as they congratulate him on his emergence as the party’s flag bearer for the 2023 presidential election. In a Statement signed by the National Coordinator of PDP Councilors who is also the National Vice President of The National Councilors’ Forum of Nigeria, Hon. Dominic Pudiya Biakpara, Deputy Coordinator Hon. Suleiman Mohammed Ibrahim(2nd Vice President NCFN) and the Secretary Hon Kusugh Terungwa said Nigerians can only breath a sigh of relief with the PDP coming on board in 2023. According to the Forum, the country is at a precipice where patriotism is at an all time low while national security has taken a steep slide. The economy is on a free fall and if the APC continues in power Nigeria will go beyond the point of no return. -Advertisement- The Forum said, “zoning is very crucial but at this time winning is most critical because we need a President that can unite the country and deliver on day one on national Security and the economy, these are key tenets of the Alhaji Atku Abubakar candidature”. They urged the PDP Presidential Candidate to select a running mate with impeccable grassroots credentials to put a balance on the ticket and advised him to put structures together with other Presidential Aspirants in the party to enthrone a PDP government at the federal level come 2023. The PDP Councilors’ Forum also commended the PDP leadership under Senator Iyorchia Ayu for conducting free, fair and credible primaries at all levels and the critical role played by the PDP Governors Forum.